claim.claim-text:
A molecule for use according to any of claims 1 to 3, wherein the siRNA is a duplex consisting of a sense strand and an antisense strand, wherein:
a) each strand is 19-24 nucleotides in length;
b) the duplex has 19-24 base pairs;
c) the antisense strand is complementary to a target RNA encoded by the BORIS gene; and
d) the sense strand and the antisense strand are complementary to each other.
